# Adboard booking camera


# Setup Streaming on Raspberry Pi

This repository contains a script (`setup_streaming.sh`) that sets up streaming on a Raspberry Pi. The script discovers RTSP streams on the local network, configures HLS streaming, and makes the stream accessible via Pitunnel.

### Steps to setup camera
git clone https://github.com/AdBoard-Booking/adboard-booking-camera
cd adboard-booking-camera

sudo apt-get install nmap

git pull origin main
sudo cp setup_streaming.sh /usr/local/bin/setup_streaming.sh
sudo cp scan_rtsp.sh /usr/local/bin/scan_rtsp.sh
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/setup_streaming.sh
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/scan_rtsp.sh

Open the cron table for the root user:

sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/setup_streaming.service

```
[Unit]
Description=Setup Streaming Service
After=network.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/setup_streaming.sh
Restart=on-failure
User=root

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable setup_streaming.service

//test
sudo systemctl start setup_streaming.service

//check
sudo systemctl status setup_streaming.service

